100
00:04:33,447 --> 00:04:35,127
What do you think
of the pattern this year?

101
00:04:35,536 --> 00:04:37,059
I think it's gorgeous. Oh.

102
00:04:37,799 --> 00:04:38,799
And...

103
00:04:39,627 --> 00:04:41,803
You were mentioned
on Ivy B. Holly,

104
00:04:41,933 --> 00:04:43,333
one of my favourite
Christmas blogs.

105
00:04:44,458 --> 00:04:47,069
"Here I go,
embarking on my second year

106
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:48,592
of Six Degrees of Santa,

107
00:04:48,723 --> 00:04:53,336
a delightful, if mysterious,
gift chain I found online.

108
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,337
Check it out!"

109
00:04:54,468 --> 00:04:56,948
Isn't that what
they call trending?

110
00:04:57,079 --> 00:04:58,230
Huh? I know I've said it before,

111
00:04:58,254 --> 00:05:01,518
but I really feel like you could
go big with this.

112
00:05:01,649 --> 00:05:03,999
I don't think that counts
as trending, Mom.

113
00:05:04,129 --> 00:05:06,393
You know what,
I've said it before,

114
00:05:06,523 --> 00:05:09,221
small and personal,
you know? Almost renegade!

115
00:05:09,352 --> 00:05:10,440
That's the whole point.

116
00:05:10,571 --> 00:05:14,575
I don't mean big
like corporate partner.

117
00:05:14,705 --> 00:05:17,273
I'm saying big, like,
get some momentum behind it.

118
00:05:17,404 --> 00:05:18,666
Find a way to get paid for it.

119
00:05:19,710 --> 00:05:22,844
Why? Are you firing me?

120
00:05:22,974 --> 00:05:25,760
No, I like having
you around too much.

121
00:05:27,152 --> 00:05:29,851
But your skills
are being underserved.

122
00:05:31,026 --> 00:05:34,421
What? Working with my mom
in our family company

123
00:05:34,551 --> 00:05:36,945
and getting to spend
more time with my daughter?

124
00:05:38,338 --> 00:05:39,658
I'd say that counts
as fulfilling.

125
00:05:41,776 --> 00:05:45,083
I suppose I'm also saying,

126
00:05:45,214 --> 00:05:47,477
who knows how much longer
this will be around.

127
00:05:50,132 --> 00:05:52,439
Do you mean that in
the philosophical sense or...

128
00:05:52,569 --> 00:05:54,005
Mom, are you worried?

129
00:05:55,224 --> 00:05:56,530
Your father was...

130
00:05:57,835 --> 00:05:59,359
better at the business side
of things.

131
00:06:01,273 --> 00:06:02,274
December just started.

132
00:06:02,405 --> 00:06:04,276
It's our busiest time.

133
00:06:05,756 --> 00:06:08,063
We just need a banner
sale season. We'll be okay.

134
00:06:08,193 --> 00:06:09,238
Okay.

135
00:06:10,805 --> 00:06:14,025
So, what do we need
for a big banner sale season?

136
00:06:14,156 --> 00:06:16,245
A rush of Christmas spirit!

137
00:06:16,898 --> 00:06:17,898
Luck.

138
00:06:19,422 --> 00:06:20,467
Oh, before you settle in,

139
00:06:20,597 --> 00:06:24,166
can you walk these packages
over to Gus?

140
00:06:24,732 --> 00:06:25,907
Please!

141
00:06:26,821 --> 00:06:28,431
- Sure, Mom.
- Thank you!

142
00:06:28,562 --> 00:06:29,824
Mm-hmm!

143
00:06:31,216 --> 00:06:33,088
Alright, let's hear it,
people, let's hear it.

144
00:06:36,439 --> 00:06:37,938
Hi, everyone.
Thank you so much for coming.

145
00:06:37,962 --> 00:06:39,660
Lovely to see you all.

146
00:06:39,790 --> 00:06:42,793
Now, I am beyond thrilled

147
00:06:42,924 --> 00:06:45,709
to bring my tech brand
into the real world

148
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:49,452
and into your living rooms
on Christmas morning with...

149
00:06:49,583 --> 00:06:50,583
SparkLTree!

150
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:54,631
Partnering with farmers,

151
00:06:54,762 --> 00:06:57,068
we have engineered
what we believe to be

152
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:59,244
the perfect Christmas tree.

153
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:03,814
From branch distribution,
shape, and needle retention,

154
00:07:03,945 --> 00:07:06,426
right down to that magnificent
conifer scent.

155
00:07:07,688 --> 00:07:09,864
Now, it comes in three sizes,

156
00:07:09,994 --> 00:07:10,994
but most importantly,

157
00:07:11,735 --> 00:07:13,955
it can be delivered
to your front door

158
00:07:14,085 --> 00:07:16,261
with the very simple
click of a button.

159
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:19,438
Are you ready?

160
00:07:24,313 --> 00:07:25,749
- Hey, Hal.
- Hey.

161
00:07:26,358 --> 00:07:27,577
What's all this?

162
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:30,711
Oh, it's a Christmas tree
you order online.

163
00:07:30,841 --> 00:07:32,713
Apparently it's perfect.

164
00:07:32,843 --> 00:07:35,716
Ugh! Jason Sparks.

165
00:07:37,369 --> 00:07:39,391
Of course he thinks he can
invade and commodify Christmas.

166
00:07:39,415 --> 00:07:42,723
Oh, I'd suppose you've known him
from your Silicon Valley days.

167
00:07:42,853 --> 00:07:43,853
Yeah, I worked for him.

168
00:07:44,768 --> 00:07:46,006
Well, I mean,
for one of his companies.

169
00:07:46,030 --> 00:07:47,554
I... I didn't know him.

170
00:07:47,684 --> 00:07:50,295
He's more of a looming presence.

171
00:07:50,426 --> 00:07:54,561
Now just think, no more
laborious trips to the farm,

172
00:07:54,691 --> 00:07:56,651
having to strap your tree
to the roof of your car,

173
00:07:56,737 --> 00:07:57,433
scratching the paint.

174
00:07:57,564 --> 00:07:59,087
And if you live in the City,

175
00:07:59,217 --> 00:08:02,743
imagine not having to haul
your cumbersome Christmas trees

176
00:08:02,873 --> 00:08:04,048
seven city blocks,

177
00:08:04,179 --> 00:08:06,747
only to have it poke you
and give you splinters,

178
00:08:07,791 --> 00:08:10,533
sap all over your hands,
needles everywhere.

179
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,405
You gotta love how he pretends

180
00:08:13,536 --> 00:08:14,189
like he's doing it
for our well-being.

181
00:08:14,319 --> 00:08:17,148
Eh, he's always been nice to me.

182
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,021
You would buy one
of those things?

183
00:08:21,109 --> 00:08:23,154
Yeah! I mean, look at it.

184
00:08:23,285 --> 00:08:24,852
It's a good-looking tree!

185
00:08:24,982 --> 00:08:26,810
But what about
your trip to Watson's Farm

186
00:08:26,941 --> 00:08:28,290
with Jeanie and the kids, huh?

187
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:30,205
And hot cocoa in travel mugs?

188
00:08:30,335 --> 00:08:31,815
Uh, maybe we could just stay in,

189
00:08:31,946 --> 00:08:33,226
watch A Christmas Carol instead?

190
00:08:33,251 --> 00:08:35,036
I don't believe it.

191
00:08:35,166 --> 00:08:36,472
To be continued!

192
00:08:36,603 --> 00:08:37,603
Alright. Have a good one.

193
00:08:39,431 --> 00:08:40,998
Right to your front door.

194
00:08:43,218 --> 00:08:45,742
Thank you so much.

195
00:08:45,873 --> 00:08:47,483
Thank you.

196
00:09:02,846 --> 00:09:04,166
Are you going
to get a SparkLTree?

197
00:09:06,807 --> 00:09:07,807
No.

198
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:13,117
Oh. You don't celebrate
Christmas. I'm so sorry,

199
00:09:13,248 --> 00:09:14,249
I shouldn't assume.

200
00:09:14,379 --> 00:09:16,251
Oh, no, no.
I celebrate Christmas.

201
00:09:16,773 --> 00:09:18,906
I adore Christmas.

202
00:09:19,036 --> 00:09:21,561
But I also adore
real Christmas trees.

203
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:25,521
SparkLTrees are real
Christmas trees.

204
00:09:25,652 --> 00:09:27,828
Also, personally, you know,
I enjoy carrying my tree

205
00:09:27,958 --> 00:09:30,047
back those seven blocks
from the tree lot.

206
00:09:30,178 --> 00:09:31,962
You know,
a family-owned business,

207
00:09:32,093 --> 00:09:34,312
something that is practically disappearing.

208
00:09:34,443 --> 00:09:36,247
And if the tree wants
to poke me with its needles,

209
00:09:36,271 --> 00:09:37,446
well, I welcome it!

210
00:09:39,143 --> 00:09:40,143
Sorry, do I know you?

211
00:09:40,841 --> 00:09:42,241
Have I done something
to offend you?

212
00:09:42,277 --> 00:09:44,845
Why bother growing
living things at all, right?

213
00:09:44,975 --> 00:09:47,325
Why not just skip ahead to,
I don't know,

214
00:09:47,456 --> 00:09:48,805
a Christmas tree hologram

215
00:09:48,936 --> 00:09:50,435
that you can decorate
from your tablet?

216
00:09:50,459 --> 00:09:52,243
That's...

217
00:09:52,374 --> 00:09:53,505
not a bad idea, actually.

218
00:09:54,855 --> 00:09:56,944
That would be
really good for travel. Hmm...

219
00:09:57,074 --> 00:09:58,685
Okay, why are you trying

220
00:09:58,815 --> 00:10:00,687
to take the heart
and magic out of Christmas?

221
00:10:02,514 --> 00:10:03,777
I think you're making a lot

222
00:10:03,907 --> 00:10:05,147
of assumptions about this tree.

223
00:10:06,344 --> 00:10:08,192
Tell you what, how about I send
you one, on the house?

224
00:10:08,216 --> 00:10:09,296
You might change your mind.

225
00:10:09,347 --> 00:10:10,435
I would send it back.

226
00:10:11,436 --> 00:10:12,612
Merry Christmas.

227
00:10:17,312 --> 00:10:18,748
Good morning, sir.

228
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:20,271
Quick question for you, Elliott.

229
00:10:20,402 --> 00:10:21,098
Yeah, go ahead. Shoot, Boss.

230
00:10:21,229 --> 00:10:22,622
Do you think the SparkLTree

231
00:10:22,752 --> 00:10:25,712
brand fails
to exude magic and heart?

232
00:10:25,842 --> 00:10:27,690
Uh, I'd say it piggybacks
off the inherent magic

233
00:10:27,714 --> 00:10:28,410
and heart of the season?

234
00:10:28,540 --> 00:10:29,700
We did have that focus group.

235
00:10:32,762 --> 00:10:36,157
So... this is your
forwarded mail.

236
00:10:36,287 --> 00:10:38,507
I checked for anything
time sensitive.

237
00:10:40,030 --> 00:10:43,991
I also wasn't sure
whether to pass this one along.

238
00:10:50,737 --> 00:10:52,086
It looks great.

239
00:10:52,826 --> 00:10:54,305
Happy.

240
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,000
I suppose it was only
a matter of time.

241
00:10:57,091 --> 00:11:00,007
Um, look up their registry
and send them something nice.

242
00:11:00,137 --> 00:11:01,137
Sure.

243
00:11:14,369 --> 00:11:15,544
Come in!

244
00:11:16,327 --> 00:11:17,459
Hey, you!

245
00:11:17,589 --> 00:11:18,709
Hey! Happy December, Harper.

246
00:11:18,765 --> 00:11:20,375
Happy December to you too!

247
00:11:21,289 --> 00:11:23,683
Dani, your dad's here!

248
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:25,835
And you guys better get moving.

249
00:11:25,859 --> 00:11:26,859
Yeah.

250
00:11:27,599 --> 00:11:29,079
Hey, I saw Six Degrees posted.

251
00:11:30,428 --> 00:11:32,953
Yes! You know, look what
I found for my gift this year.

252
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:34,083
- Wow!
- Mm-hmm!

253
00:11:34,171 --> 00:11:36,173
And... you're going
to give it away?

254
00:11:36,304 --> 00:11:38,915
Well, yeah. I mean, it's the
perfect thing for Six Degrees.

255
00:11:39,046 --> 00:11:41,439
You know, nobody knows it,
so it's new,

256
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:42,876
but it's also timeless.

257
00:11:43,006 --> 00:11:44,704
And, you know, it's about
human connection.

258
00:11:45,835 --> 00:11:47,315
It basically inspired
the whole thing.

259
00:11:53,887 --> 00:11:54,887
What's up?

260
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,980
Speaking of human connection,

261
00:12:02,417 --> 00:12:03,940
I've met somebody.

262
00:12:05,420 --> 00:12:07,380
And I really feel like
it's going to go somewhere.

263
00:12:07,770 --> 00:12:08,770
Her name's Sylvia.

264
00:12:10,164 --> 00:12:11,228
And I wanted to introduce her

265
00:12:11,252 --> 00:12:14,429
to Dani but I wanted
to talk to you first.

266
00:12:14,559 --> 00:12:16,170
I trust your timing
and judgment.

267
00:12:17,954 --> 00:12:19,086
I'm happy for you.

268
00:12:20,827 --> 00:12:21,827
How about you?

269
00:12:23,046 --> 00:12:24,371
Anything going on
in that department?

270
00:12:24,395 --> 00:12:26,789
No. Nope, no.

271
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:28,008
I'm, uh...

272
00:12:28,138 --> 00:12:30,184
I'm putting all of that
on the back burner...

273
00:12:30,314 --> 00:12:31,402
Hey, Dad!

274
00:12:31,533 --> 00:12:35,102
Hey, look at you!

275
00:12:35,232 --> 00:12:36,552
Are we excited
for The Nutcracker?

276
00:12:36,625 --> 00:12:37,931
So excited!

277
00:12:39,497 --> 00:12:41,301
See, I wonder if he'll beat
the Mouse King this year.

278
00:12:41,325 --> 00:12:43,240
Dad! He always does.

279
00:12:43,371 --> 00:12:44,502
Come on, let's go.

280
00:13:17,013 --> 00:13:18,013
<i>Dear Santas,</i>

281
00:13:22,497 --> 00:13:25,326
<i>this book holds a special
place in my heart.</i>

282
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,421
I decided to go with
the Jingle Mice record.

283
00:13:33,551 --> 00:13:34,770
Oh, that's perfect!

284
00:13:34,901 --> 00:13:36,748
Do you know how many people
are going to be listening

285
00:13:36,772 --> 00:13:38,092
to your favourite
Christmas music?

286
00:13:38,992 --> 00:13:40,820
And, uh, do you have
a Santa #2 in mind?

287
00:13:41,995 --> 00:13:43,605
There's this new girl
in my class.

288
00:13:43,735 --> 00:13:45,650
She's really shy. How about you?

289
00:13:46,695 --> 00:13:47,827
You know, this year,

290
00:13:47,957 --> 00:13:49,785
I think I'm going
to be in the moment,

291
00:13:49,916 --> 00:13:51,178
go where inspiration takes me!

292
00:13:58,402 --> 00:13:59,099
Good morning, Leonard!

293
00:13:59,229 --> 00:14:00,927
Good morning, you two!

294
00:14:01,057 --> 00:14:02,687
Oh, it's the start
of your busy season, huh?

295
00:14:02,711 --> 00:14:05,540
Yes, but I love it.

296
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:07,237
It probably sounds
kind of cheesy,

297
00:14:07,368 --> 00:14:09,805
but this time of year,
it feels extra special

298
00:14:09,936 --> 00:14:12,895
to be the person who connects
the people with the packages.

299
00:14:13,026 --> 00:14:14,505
And cards.

300
00:14:14,636 --> 00:14:16,246
It makes me feel
like a V.I.P.

301
00:14:16,377 --> 00:14:18,553
- Mm-hmm!
- Very important postman!

302
00:14:36,745 --> 00:14:37,745
Huh...

303
00:14:42,707 --> 00:14:44,622
Hey, come on,

304
00:14:44,753 --> 00:14:45,753
let's read the book.

305
00:14:46,973 --> 00:14:47,756
Jump up.

306
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:49,018
Yeah.

307
00:14:49,149 --> 00:14:50,498
What are these people doing?

308
00:14:51,716 --> 00:14:52,716
Thank you.

309
00:14:52,761 --> 00:14:54,067
And this is for you.

310
00:14:55,372 --> 00:14:58,071
♪ Craving to hold your hand

311
00:14:58,985 --> 00:15:01,901
♪ Six degrees of love

312
00:15:06,557 --> 00:15:09,038
♪ Coming from different worlds

313
00:15:10,039 --> 00:15:12,259
♪ Still would feel the same

314
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:15,915
♪ Six degrees from us

315
00:15:18,265 --> 00:15:20,180
This is for Mr. Sparks.
He gets to keep it!

316
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:27,665
So, Christmas
is fast approaching,

317
00:15:27,796 --> 00:15:30,407
but we are pretty much
wrapped on SparkLTree.

318
00:15:30,538 --> 00:15:33,845
Um... We deployed the updates
to the companion app.

319
00:15:33,976 --> 00:15:36,283
Music Department has added
a few extra playlists.

320
00:15:36,413 --> 00:15:38,633
For example,
"Music to open presents to."

321
00:15:40,330 --> 00:15:44,204
And, of course, there's tree
care, wrapping tips, et cetera.

322
00:15:44,334 --> 00:15:46,902
So, uh, we should be all
good to go for your hiatus.

323
00:15:49,209 --> 00:15:50,906
Hiatus...

324
00:15:51,037 --> 00:15:53,256
Oh, there was this bake sale

325
00:15:53,387 --> 00:15:55,606
sponsorship for a local high
school basketball team

326
00:15:55,737 --> 00:15:57,217
coming this Saturday night.

327
00:15:57,347 --> 00:15:58,392
It's really small scale.

328
00:15:58,522 --> 00:16:00,239
I'm not even sure how
the request got through.

329
00:16:00,263 --> 00:16:01,414
Do you just want
me to cancel on that...

330
00:16:01,438 --> 00:16:02,135
No.

331
00:16:02,265 --> 00:16:03,832
No.

332
00:16:05,834 --> 00:16:07,986
That would go against the sincere,
down-to-earth vibe we're going for.

333
00:16:08,010 --> 00:16:09,945
No, put Fabian on it.
You can coordinate remotely.

334
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:10,969
Okay.

335
00:16:13,668 --> 00:16:15,602
Are you sure I should be
heading to Vermont tomorrow?

336
00:16:15,626 --> 00:16:16,647
Enjoy your time
with your family.

337
00:16:16,671 --> 00:16:17,454
I mean, don't forget

338
00:16:17,585 --> 00:16:19,152
to take notes on the authentic

339
00:16:19,282 --> 00:16:21,458
family Christmas
for SparkLTree 2.0.

340
00:16:23,330 --> 00:16:25,850
But you haven't spent Christmas
with your family in three years.

341
00:16:26,942 --> 00:16:28,988
I feel like it's something
you should do, yeah.

342
00:16:32,078 --> 00:16:33,862
Uh, is everything okay?

343
00:16:36,647 --> 00:16:38,127
I think so.

344
00:16:38,258 --> 00:16:41,043
Just that off feeling, you know?

345
00:16:41,174 --> 00:16:44,264
Mmm. I'm sure
it's your open calendar.

346
00:16:44,394 --> 00:16:45,700
You're not used to it.

347
00:16:45,830 --> 00:16:47,136
I think it's a good thing.

348
00:16:47,267 --> 00:16:49,921
I mean, everyone needs
to take time off at some point.

349
00:16:50,052 --> 00:16:52,272
And Christmas is as good
a time as any to...

350
00:16:53,925 --> 00:16:57,886
Reminds me, um, that box over
there is an actual present.

351
00:16:58,843 --> 00:17:00,584
Yeah, Hal passed it along,

352
00:17:00,715 --> 00:17:03,892
said some boy who's a fan
wanted to give it to you.

353
00:17:06,242 --> 00:17:07,242
Thank you.

354
00:17:43,932 --> 00:17:44,932
<i>Dear Santas,</i>

355
00:17:46,195 --> 00:17:48,371
<i>this book holds a special place
in my heart.</i>

356
00:17:49,546 --> 00:17:52,071
<i>My father gave me a copy
when I was a child.</i>

357
00:17:53,637 --> 00:17:57,380
<i>I miss him so much,
especially this time of year.</i>

358
00:17:57,511 --> 00:18:00,862
<i>But the very book he gave me
always reminds me</i>

359
00:18:00,992 --> 00:18:05,780
<i>that there is love and
connection to be had everywher.</i>

360
00:18:06,563 --> 00:18:08,435
<i>Maybe even right
around the corner.</i>

361
00:18:09,392 --> 00:18:11,090
<i>I wish all of this for you.</i>

362
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:14,702
<i>Yours, Ms. Santa #1.</i>

363
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:23,885
This very book,

364
00:18:25,321 --> 00:18:27,584
it was like a lifeline for me
when I was young.

365
00:18:29,064 --> 00:18:31,464
My family, they moved constantly
and my uncle got this for me

366
00:18:31,588 --> 00:18:36,202
to remind me that home didn't
necessarily need to be a place.

367
00:18:37,855 --> 00:18:40,336
I lost my copy and I've been
looking for one ever since.

368
00:18:40,467 --> 00:18:41,859
And then it just shows up!

369
00:18:42,469 --> 00:18:44,514
And the note on the inside...

370
00:18:45,863 --> 00:18:49,128
it feels like it was
written by me, or for me.

371
00:18:50,694 --> 00:18:54,698
So... are we looking into
a publishing venture or...

372
00:18:54,829 --> 00:18:57,788
The fact that this found me at a
time where I'm taking a break to...

373
00:19:01,401 --> 00:19:03,707
process how I'm feeling
about my ex getting married.

374
00:19:03,838 --> 00:19:07,407
So, are we looking
to get back into dating apps?

375
00:19:07,537 --> 00:19:08,669
Cancelling your hiatus?

376
00:19:08,799 --> 00:19:09,959
This isn't about the company.

377
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,500
All I know is...

378
00:19:15,806 --> 00:19:17,460
when I read this note
in this book,

379
00:19:18,374 --> 00:19:20,594
I felt something
I haven't felt in years.

380
00:19:21,812 --> 00:19:23,292
With all those
coincidences lining up,

381
00:19:23,379 --> 00:19:24,922
I feel like it would
be negligent not to follow

382
00:19:24,946 --> 00:19:26,513
the data,
to see where this leads.

383
00:19:28,254 --> 00:19:31,170
I have to find, to meet...

384
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:34,521
Ms. Santa #1.

385
00:19:40,266 --> 00:19:42,069
I just have to say,
a few of us have really been

386
00:19:42,093 --> 00:19:43,773
rooting for you to get back
out there, sir.

387
00:19:44,748 --> 00:19:47,534
Okay, it looks like
this is the website.

388
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:52,495
It's like a chain letter,
but with gifting?

389
00:19:53,670 --> 00:19:55,411
It is pretty clever,
if underdeveloped.

390
00:19:56,891 --> 00:19:58,216
There's gotta be some kind
of social media component

391
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:00,111
for all these Santas
to meet each other.

392
00:20:00,677 --> 00:20:02,984
Uh, I don't see anything.

393
00:20:04,072 --> 00:20:05,726
Let's watch this video.

394
00:20:07,336 --> 00:20:09,416
<i>Hello, everyone, and welcome
to Six Degrees of Santa.</i>

395
00:20:09,860 --> 00:20:10,644
<i>It's December first...</i>

396
00:20:10,774 --> 00:20:11,774
Wait a second.

397
00:20:12,123 --> 00:20:13,124
I've met this woman!

398
00:20:13,255 --> 00:20:15,083
Yeah, didn't she used
to work for us?

399
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:18,086
Wait, what?

400
00:20:23,744 --> 00:20:26,877
I saw that you put
in for more boxes.

401
00:20:27,008 --> 00:20:28,507
Are you still shipping
those out, free of charge?

402
00:20:28,531 --> 00:20:31,447
Yeah! You know,
I actually mailed one off

403
00:20:31,578 --> 00:20:34,407
to Skagway, Alaska
the other day. Yeah!

404
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:37,671
That's gotta start
adding up, sweetheart.

405
00:20:38,498 --> 00:20:40,543
Well, you know,
sometimes people choose

406
00:20:40,674 --> 00:20:43,329
to spend their money going
to Aspen for the holidays,

407
00:20:43,459 --> 00:20:44,979
but this is how
I choose to spend mind.

408
00:20:45,896 --> 00:20:46,960
Plus, you know,
it drives foot traffic

409
00:20:46,984 --> 00:20:49,509
to the store, so I think
it's win-win.

410
00:20:49,639 --> 00:20:50,771
Harper McNevin.

411
00:20:52,163 --> 00:20:53,208
You used to work for me.

412
00:20:54,383 --> 00:20:56,472
Hmm, yeah, have you popped by

413
00:20:56,603 --> 00:20:57,963
for a forgotten
performance review?

414
00:21:00,041 --> 00:21:00,737
Hi, I'm Jason Sparks.

415
00:21:00,868 --> 00:21:02,086
Oh, I know! Hi.

416
00:21:02,217 --> 00:21:04,175
I'm Pauline, Harper's mother.

417
00:21:05,220 --> 00:21:07,135
This is Elliott,
my executive assistant.

418
00:21:08,745 --> 00:21:10,399
I looked into it.

419
00:21:10,530 --> 00:21:13,272
You were one of our most
promising programmers.

420
00:21:13,402 --> 00:21:16,579
You designed Sugar Share,
charming neighborhood sharing app.

421
00:21:16,710 --> 00:21:20,061
Yeah, which your VP
of Business Development squelched

422
00:21:20,191 --> 00:21:22,629
because it didn't have enough
profit potential.

423
00:21:22,759 --> 00:21:24,587
Yeah, that happens.

424
00:21:24,718 --> 00:21:25,719
Why are you here?

425
00:21:26,937 --> 00:21:28,983
Uh... and how did you find me?

426
00:21:29,113 --> 00:21:30,201
Well, as a matter of fact,

427
00:21:30,332 --> 00:21:34,554
I am a Santa #6 in
your Six Degrees of Santa chain.

428
00:21:34,684 --> 00:21:37,513
Your video indicated
I might find you here,

429
00:21:37,644 --> 00:21:41,300
and well, I was hoping you could
help me locate my original Santa.

430
00:21:42,126 --> 00:21:43,389
This is the gift I received.

431
00:21:45,565 --> 00:21:46,805
Would you look at that!
That's...

432
00:21:46,914 --> 00:21:48,132
A book. Yeah, Mom.

433
00:21:48,263 --> 00:21:50,309
It's a book that I've never
seen before in my life.

434
00:21:51,875 --> 00:21:55,314
So why do you have to find
this original Santa?

435
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:59,274
Well, it's important to me.

436
00:22:01,711 --> 00:22:04,105
This book was a childhood
favourite of mine.

437
00:22:05,672 --> 00:22:08,022
That, along with the note
written on the inside the cover,

438
00:22:08,936 --> 00:22:09,719
well, it made me think

439
00:22:09,850 --> 00:22:12,766
that we might possibly
share a...

440
00:22:13,897 --> 00:22:14,897
a connection.

441
00:22:15,638 --> 00:22:16,813
You mean like romantically?

442
00:22:16,944 --> 00:22:18,815
Possibly. Maybe.

443
00:22:20,164 --> 00:22:22,273
Listen, I got a gut-feeling
and I simply can't ignore it.

444
00:22:22,297 --> 00:22:25,082
Huh... I'm going to go inside.

445
00:22:25,213 --> 00:22:26,649
I'm sure that I heard the phone.

446
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:31,132
Well, I can't help you.

447
00:22:31,262 --> 00:22:34,135
The spirit of Six Degrees
is one of anonymity.

448
00:22:34,265 --> 00:22:35,658
Well, speaking of that,

449
00:22:35,789 --> 00:22:38,029
I actually have an enticing
thing to offer you in return.

450
00:22:39,183 --> 00:22:41,360
See, I think Six Degrees
has a lot of potential.

451
00:22:42,796 --> 00:22:43,796
Not interested.

452
00:22:51,413 --> 00:22:53,043
I could help you make it
a household name,

453
00:22:53,067 --> 00:22:54,392
along the lines
of "White Elephant."

454
00:22:54,416 --> 00:22:57,419
We could loop in
investors, sponsors.

455
00:22:57,550 --> 00:22:59,247
And we just got
that quick analysis back.

456
00:23:00,727 --> 00:23:02,767
It would be an advantageous
follow up to SparkLTree.

457
00:23:03,686 --> 00:23:05,732
Definitely not interested.

458
00:23:06,472 --> 00:23:07,821
That's not what
the site's about.

459
00:23:07,951 --> 00:23:11,085
Though, I don't recall
seeing a copyright.

460
00:23:13,783 --> 00:23:15,239
Which means there's
nothing to stop us from

461
00:23:15,263 --> 00:23:16,503
just taking off with it anyway.

462
00:23:17,526 --> 00:23:18,526
Is that a threat?

463
00:23:19,789 --> 00:23:22,226
No, I'm just thinking out loud.

464
00:23:22,357 --> 00:23:24,161
There's gotta be some way
I can convince you to help me

465
00:23:24,185 --> 00:23:25,360
find Ms. Santa #1.

466
00:23:27,884 --> 00:23:30,757
Wait, which is it that you
want? Ms. Santa or Six Degrees?

467
00:23:31,497 --> 00:23:33,107
Well, both.

468
00:23:35,065 --> 00:23:38,286
I'm just hoping we could make a
deal, you know, help each other.

469
00:23:39,635 --> 00:23:41,507
If you really want
to help people,

470
00:23:41,637 --> 00:23:43,596
maybe help some
of the small businesses

471
00:23:43,726 --> 00:23:45,511
that your industry
is destroying.

472
00:23:45,641 --> 00:23:47,774
You mean like this one?
Sure! Easy-peasy.

473
00:23:49,558 --> 00:23:50,820
I'll tell you what.

474
00:23:50,951 --> 00:23:53,257
You help me find
Ms. Santa #1,

475
00:23:54,607 --> 00:23:56,478
I'll help with your foot traffic
and marketing.

476
00:23:57,871 --> 00:24:00,134
McNevin Paper Company
will see unprecedented sales.

477
00:24:02,353 --> 00:24:05,748
Well, I mean, what if we can't
find Ms. Santa #1?

478
00:24:05,879 --> 00:24:09,056
You know, or we do
and she's like 99 years old

479
00:24:09,186 --> 00:24:12,799
or, you know, loathes
your very existence?

480
00:24:12,929 --> 00:24:15,454
I mean, do our terms
still stand?

481
00:24:15,584 --> 00:24:17,630
Sure. I don't think it'll
be any of those scenarios.

482
00:24:18,848 --> 00:24:20,284
Okay, so to confirm,

483
00:24:21,416 --> 00:24:23,810
you help boost McNevin Paper
Company sales,

484
00:24:23,940 --> 00:24:26,073
and you leave Six Degrees alone.

485
00:24:26,203 --> 00:24:28,510
No push for growth from you
or any of your companies.

486
00:24:29,816 --> 00:24:30,880
This is the weirdest deal
I've ever made.

487
00:24:30,904 --> 00:24:31,905
Oh, just promise!

488
00:24:32,035 --> 00:24:34,168
I promise.

489
00:24:38,912 --> 00:24:39,912
It's a deal.

490
00:24:44,221 --> 00:24:45,484
Elliott.

491
00:24:51,751 --> 00:24:55,189
So you made a deal
with him to find you.

492
00:24:55,885 --> 00:24:57,408
Correct.

493
00:24:57,539 --> 00:24:59,323
Look, I was this whirlwind
of confusion!

494
00:24:59,454 --> 00:25:01,674
You know, at first, I wanted
to protect Six Degrees,

495
00:25:01,804 --> 00:25:03,893
but then he mentioned helping
the shop,

496
00:25:04,938 --> 00:25:06,538
and I was mad I didn't
think of it first.

497
00:25:07,157 --> 00:25:08,158
Well, you have been known

498
00:25:08,289 --> 00:25:10,334
to occasionally miss
the forest for the trees.

499
00:25:10,465 --> 00:25:12,423
Mmm... For the SparkLTrees.

500
00:25:14,469 --> 00:25:15,775
- Option one...
- Yeah.

501
00:25:15,905 --> 00:25:17,472
You come clean
and you tell him that

502
00:25:17,603 --> 00:25:19,039
the mystery match is you.

503
00:25:20,170 --> 00:25:21,170
Just see where it goes!

504
00:25:21,258 --> 00:25:23,347
No! Definitely not.

505
00:25:24,871 --> 00:25:27,311
Everything about him goes against
everything that I care about.

506
00:25:28,091 --> 00:25:29,615
And I feel it would
nullify the deal.

507
00:25:29,745 --> 00:25:32,158
You know, why work up all of these
terms only to turn around and say,

508
00:25:32,182 --> 00:25:33,923
"Hey, guess what? It's me!
