1511
01:19:27,414 --> 01:19:28,676
at this point of no return.

1512
01:19:28,807 --> 01:19:30,026
Mm-hmm.

1513
01:19:34,291 --> 01:19:36,772
Elliott, what are you doing
here?

1514
01:19:36,902 --> 01:19:38,686
I am so sorry to interrupt.

1515
01:19:38,817 --> 01:19:41,602
I saw this reservation
in your calendar

1516
01:19:41,733 --> 01:19:44,301
and you haven't been answering
the phone so I started to worry

1517
01:19:44,431 --> 01:19:46,956
but I, uh...

1518
01:19:48,087 --> 01:19:49,654
suppose I can see why.

1519
01:19:50,960 --> 01:19:53,049
I wanted to make sure
you were alive,

1520
01:19:53,179 --> 01:19:56,792
and if you were alive,
which you are,

1521
01:19:56,922 --> 01:20:00,578
to tell you that I think
I messed things up with Harper.

1522
01:20:00,708 --> 01:20:03,755
I called her to see
if she'd heard from you

1523
01:20:03,886 --> 01:20:05,472
and I didn't know
I wasn't supposed to bring up

1524
01:20:05,496 --> 01:20:07,280
the copyright.

1525
01:20:07,411 --> 01:20:09,805
It's quite alright.
It doesn't matter anymore.

1526
01:20:11,154 --> 01:20:12,914
Zoey, this is my executive
assistant Elliott.

1527
01:20:13,025 --> 01:20:14,679
Elliott, this is Zoey.

1528
01:20:16,333 --> 01:20:18,161
Please, have a seat. Join us.

1529
01:20:20,293 --> 01:20:22,948
I thought it was the book that
was supposed to be a secret.

1530
01:20:24,689 --> 01:20:27,300
Oh, no, it was supposed to be
a secret from her, wasn't it?

1531
01:20:27,431 --> 01:20:28,998
No, no. Harper.

1532
01:20:30,564 --> 01:20:32,455
I'm having Northbound Elf
republished in hardback

1533
01:20:32,479 --> 01:20:33,654
for Harper.

1534
01:20:33,785 --> 01:20:35,831
Wait, it wasn't for Zoey?

1535
01:20:38,703 --> 01:20:40,531
Uh, no.

1536
01:20:44,622 --> 01:20:46,885
In the end, Harper deceived me,

1537
01:20:47,016 --> 01:20:50,410
but it led to you,
me and Zoey here

1538
01:20:50,541 --> 01:20:52,195
on this lovely date right now.

1539
01:20:53,109 --> 01:20:55,459
But, let's face it,

1540
01:20:55,589 --> 01:20:57,389
I'm not the person
you're supposed to be with.

1541
01:20:57,461 --> 01:20:59,985
No, no, you are.

1542
01:21:00,116 --> 01:21:02,205
You're falling in love
with her, aren't you?

1543
01:21:04,424 --> 01:21:07,079
You are falling
in love with Harper!

1544
01:21:08,646 --> 01:21:10,319
You and I meant well,
but we have terrible chemistry.

1545
01:21:10,343 --> 01:21:12,128
And Northbound Elf
did nothing for me.

1546
01:21:13,956 --> 01:21:15,479
Now all the weight's
off my chest.

1547
01:21:16,219 --> 01:21:17,220
I'm...

1548
01:21:19,048 --> 01:21:20,484
falling in love with Harper.

1549
01:21:20,614 --> 01:21:22,921
Oh! Harper's fantastic.

1550
01:21:23,052 --> 01:21:25,030
I've been trying to get her
to open herself up to dating

1551
01:21:25,054 --> 01:21:26,490
for so long.

1552
01:21:26,620 --> 01:21:28,622
You two would be adorbs.

1553
01:21:28,753 --> 01:21:30,537
And he's actually
double in love with her,

1554
01:21:30,668 --> 01:21:33,323
first as Miss Santa #1,
and now in real life.

1555
01:21:33,453 --> 01:21:35,891
Great point, Elliott.

1556
01:21:37,980 --> 01:21:39,895
So, what happens now?

1557
01:21:40,765 --> 01:21:41,766
Nothing.

1558
01:21:42,854 --> 01:21:44,900
She doesn't feel the same way.

1559
01:21:46,597 --> 01:21:49,077
She went to the end of the earth
to keep me from finding out...

1560
01:21:50,166 --> 01:21:52,603
she was the person
I was actually looking for.

1561
01:21:52,733 --> 01:21:55,214
Well, do you think she knows
how you feel about her?

1562
01:21:55,345 --> 01:21:57,236
What about the republication,
how did that go over?

1563
01:21:57,260 --> 01:21:59,175
It hasn't yet,
I haven't had ti...

1564
01:22:04,136 --> 01:22:05,136
I've gotta go.

1565
01:22:05,181 --> 01:22:06,922
Um, thank you both.

1566
01:22:08,010 --> 01:22:10,926
Elliott, you stay.

1567
01:22:12,101 --> 01:22:13,101
Yeah.

1568
01:22:13,189 --> 01:22:15,147
Dinner's on me.

1569
01:22:15,278 --> 01:22:17,628
- Uh...
- Okay you kids, gotta go.

1570
01:22:18,629 --> 01:22:20,152
Good luck! Merry Christmas!

1571
01:22:23,721 --> 01:22:25,636
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

1572
01:22:30,684 --> 01:22:31,859
Hey.

1573
01:22:31,990 --> 01:22:33,470
Hey.

1574
01:22:35,254 --> 01:22:36,777
Sylvia's wonderful, Derrick.

1575
01:22:36,908 --> 01:22:39,389
I'm partial to her myself.

1576
01:22:40,651 --> 01:22:42,392
How are things going
with Santa Claus?

1577
01:22:44,350 --> 01:22:46,309
It didn't work out.

1578
01:22:46,439 --> 01:22:49,312
And I think it's for the better.

1579
01:22:51,749 --> 01:22:55,666
So, uh, I'm to assume
that you headed it off.

1580
01:22:56,797 --> 01:22:58,364
And I guess it's safe to assume

1581
01:22:58,495 --> 01:23:00,845
that Dani's at least
part of your excuse?

1582
01:23:03,674 --> 01:23:06,068
Because the thing
about Dani is...

1583
01:23:06,198 --> 01:23:07,591
she's growing up.

1584
01:23:09,158 --> 01:23:11,334
She's getting wiser,
more perceptive.

1585
01:23:11,464 --> 01:23:12,813
Listen, at some point,

1586
01:23:12,944 --> 01:23:14,946
it will be less about
protecting her and more about

1587
01:23:15,077 --> 01:23:16,948
setting a good example.

1588
01:23:17,079 --> 01:23:19,516
Hey, remember that big fight
we got into in college?

1589
01:23:19,646 --> 01:23:21,822
And that big gesture
that I made,

1590
01:23:21,953 --> 01:23:24,129
singing to you from your window
of our biology class,

1591
01:23:24,260 --> 01:23:25,826
remember that?
Yes.

1592
01:23:25,957 --> 01:23:27,872
Right.
Well, I've been outdone.

1593
01:23:29,656 --> 01:23:31,049
Santa Claus posted something

1594
01:23:31,180 --> 01:23:32,740
that I think you might
be interested in.

1595
01:23:34,879 --> 01:23:36,228
Press play.

1596
01:23:36,359 --> 01:23:38,187
Yeah.

1597
01:23:38,317 --> 01:23:40,885
<i>I'd say it's less
of a business venture</i>

1598
01:23:41,016 --> 01:23:44,236
<i>and more of a gift to someone
very important to me.</i>

1599
01:23:45,716 --> 01:23:47,892
Because Northbound Elf
is very special to her too.

1600
01:23:49,589 --> 01:23:52,331
<i>It's a book about finding home
where you least suspect it.</i>

1601
01:23:53,028 --> 01:23:54,899
<i>And I found home with her.</i>

1602
01:23:59,121 --> 01:24:00,383
Oh...

1603
01:24:01,775 --> 01:24:03,777
I... I've gotta go.

1604
01:24:10,784 --> 01:24:12,134
Hi.

1605
01:24:12,264 --> 01:24:13,744
Hey.

1606
01:24:15,833 --> 01:24:18,923
Is this for Zoey?

1607
01:24:20,272 --> 01:24:24,755
No, actually,
it's for Miss Santa #1.

1608
01:24:26,365 --> 01:24:29,977
Thought it would remind her
of her favourite part

1609
01:24:30,108 --> 01:24:32,067
of her favourite book.

1610
01:24:36,419 --> 01:24:37,768
It is.

1611
01:24:39,117 --> 01:24:41,250
I'm sorry that
it's not fully wrapped,

1612
01:24:41,380 --> 01:24:43,730
I ran out of wrapping paper
and my favourite paper store

1613
01:24:43,861 --> 01:24:45,428
was closed early today.

1614
01:24:47,038 --> 01:24:49,954
I just saw your post.

1615
01:24:50,085 --> 01:24:52,348
It was...

1616
01:24:52,478 --> 01:24:54,219
I was inspired.

1617
01:24:58,223 --> 01:25:01,444
I need you to know that
I was not after Six Degrees.

1618
01:25:01,574 --> 01:25:04,534
I wanted to secure a copyright
but I wanted to do it for you,

1619
01:25:04,664 --> 01:25:06,449
to protect your idea.

1620
01:25:06,579 --> 01:25:08,103
And...

1621
01:25:09,930 --> 01:25:13,238
I also included a prototype.

1622
01:25:13,369 --> 01:25:15,849
You can think of it as
a type of scaffolding.

1623
01:25:15,980 --> 01:25:19,288
And you can go in there,
and play around,

1624
01:25:19,418 --> 01:25:21,159
and change things if you want.

1625
01:25:21,290 --> 01:25:23,509
Or nothing at all,
it's up to you.

1626
01:25:23,640 --> 01:25:25,207
But, um...

1627
01:25:25,337 --> 01:25:28,645
I was just hoping
that we could be partners.

1628
01:25:32,475 --> 01:25:34,259
I...

1629
01:25:34,390 --> 01:25:37,567
I think you were right
about opening up Six Degrees

1630
01:25:38,655 --> 01:25:40,657
and...

1631
01:25:40,787 --> 01:25:42,659
I want to do that with you.

1632
01:25:44,226 --> 01:25:47,359
I thought I was protecting it,
but I was actually

1633
01:25:47,490 --> 01:25:50,101
holding it back
from so much potential.

1634
01:25:51,276 --> 01:25:53,409
I think the same
might go for my heart.

1635
01:25:55,019 --> 01:25:58,327
I'm sorry I didn't tell you
that I was Santa #1.

1636
01:25:58,457 --> 01:26:00,067
At first I thought you were

1637
01:26:00,198 --> 01:26:01,598
the last person
in the world for me,

1638
01:26:01,721 --> 01:26:03,177
and then that became
less and less the case

1639
01:26:03,201 --> 01:26:04,855
until...

1640
01:26:04,985 --> 01:26:06,683
you were the only one for me.

1641
01:26:25,876 --> 01:26:27,356
I think this is another
great argument

1642
01:26:27,486 --> 01:26:29,053
for opening up Six Degrees.

1643
01:26:30,576 --> 01:26:33,231
I think you might be
right about that, partner.

